cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC

Reasoning: The paper deals with Neural Architecture Search (NAS) for computer vision tasks, specifically on CIFAR-10 and ImageNet datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method for efficient NAS, which involves pruning the search space dynamically, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a joint categorical distribution for sampling architectures, which is related to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks for NAS also falls under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
